ary\", \"score\": 0.9931432131976681, \"rank\": 0.004548441904235802, \"text\": \"Hungarians\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Only the Individual Neutral Athletes\", \"from\": 1522, \"to\": 1558}, {\"ngram\": \"97 per cent\", \"from\": 1624, \"to\": 1635}]}, {\"sentence\": \"World Aquatics said on Tuesday that Chinese swimmers competing in Paris have been tested \\\"on average 21 times each since January 1\\\", compared to six times for the Americans, five for the Italians, four for the Australians, British and French.\", \"from\": 1638, \"to\": 1880, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1674, \"end\": 1681, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"score\": 0.5943451762467384, \"rank\": 0.5988511261926535, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1704, \"end\": 1709, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999850116441887, \"rank\": 1.4988580514607192e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1825, \"end\": 1833, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_Italy\", \"score\": 0.7213284608557446, \"rank\": 0.2956924549297532, \"text\": \"Italians\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_Italy\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"World Aquatics\", \"from\": 1638, \"to\": 1652}, {\"ngram\": \"Tuesday\", \"from\": 1661, \"to\": 1668}, {\"ngram\": \"January\", \"from\": 1759, \"to\": 1766}, {\"ngram\": \"six times\", \"from\": 1783, \"to\": 1792}, {\"ngram\": \"the Americans\", \"from\": 1797, \"to\": 1810}, {\"ngram\": \"the Australians\", \"from\": 1844, \"to\": 1859}, {\"ngram\": \"French\", \"from\": 1873, \"to\": 1879}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ITA's list showed that the only delegation to undergo 100 per cent testing were AIN entrants - made of Russian and Belarusians - although, at the last count, there are just 33 of them.\", \"from\": 1882, \"to\": 2066, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1882, \"end\": 1885, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.5376527411614767, \"rank\": 0.8314357384551827, \"text\": \"ITA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}, {\"begin\": 1962, \"end\": 1965, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Independent_Network\", \"score\": 0.9999999980918801, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"AIN\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Independent_Network\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Independent_Network\"}, {\"begin\": 1997, \"end\": 2008, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belarusians\", \"score\": 0.9999996746060408, \"rank\": 3.2539399807312915e-07, \"text\": \"Belarusians\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belarusians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belarusians\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the only delegation\", \"from\": 1905, \"to\": 1924}, {\"ngram\": \"cent\", \"from\": 1944, \"to\": 1948}, {\"ngram\": \"the last count\", \"from\": 2024, \"to\": 2038}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, only 63 per cent of footballers have been tested.\", \"from\": 2068, \"to\": 2128, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"only 63 per cent\", \"from\": 2079, \"to\": 2095}, {\"ngram\": \"footballers\", \"from\": 2099, \"to\": 2110}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Global football federation FIFA is one of the few international bodies not to have entrusted their anti-doping program to the ITA.\", \"from\": 2130, \"to\": 2260, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2157, \"end\": 2161